1: 상관계수 검정

#########################################################
######################회귀분석/분산분석##################
#########################################################
kor <- c(42,38,51,53,40,37,41,29,52,39,45,34,
         47,35,44,48,47,30,29,34) 
eng <- c(30,25,34,35,31,29,33,23,36,30,32,29,
         34,30,28,29,33,24,30,30)

cor(kor,eng)  #  표본상관계수
## [1] 0.7567478
cor.test(kor,eng)  # 상관분석
## 
##  Pearson's product-moment correlation
## 
## data:  kor and eng
## t = 4.9114, df = 18, p-value = 0.0001125
## alternative hypothesis: true correlation is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  0.4724342 0.8984115
## sample estimates:
##       cor 
## 0.7567478
## 2: 상관계수 검정(conti.)
par(cex.lab=2,cex.axis=2)
plot(kor,eng)

5: 회귀계수의 추정

lm(eng ~ kor)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = eng ~ kor)
## 
## Coefficients:
## (Intercept)          kor  
##     15.9899       0.3499
lm(eng ~ kor-1)  # 절편 제외
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = eng ~ kor - 1)
## 
## Coefficients:
##    kor  
## 0.7299
lm(eng ~ 0 + kor)  # 절편 제외
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = eng ~ 0 + kor)
## 
## Coefficients:
##    kor  
## 0.7299

6: 선형회귀분석의 결과(그래프)

fit1=lm(eng~kor)
plot(kor,eng)
abline(fit1,col="blue")

7: 선형회귀분석의 결과

coef(fit1)  # 회귀계수
## (Intercept)         kor 
##  15.9898501   0.3499423
fitted(fit1)[1:6]  # fitted values
##        1        2        3        4        5        6 
## 30.68743 29.28766 33.83691 34.53679 29.98754 28.93772
round(residuals(fit1)[1:6],2)  # 잔차
##     1     2     3     4     5     6 
## -0.69 -4.29  0.16  0.46  1.01  0.06
fitted(fit1)[1:6] + residuals(fit1)[1:6]  # must equal to 'eng' 
##  1  2  3  4  5  6 
## 30 25 34 35 31 29
eng[1:6]
## [1] 30 25 34 35 31 29
## 8: 선형회귀분석의 결과(conti.)
confint(fit1)  # 계수의 신뢰구간
##                 2.5 %     97.5 %
## (Intercept) 9.7911231 22.1885771
## kor         0.2002491  0.4996355
deviance(fit1)  # 잔차제곱합
## [1] 99.03437
sum((eng-fitted(fit1))^2)  # 잔차제곱합. 위와 동일한 결과.
## [1] 99.03437

9: 예측

predict(fit1,newdata=data.frame(kor=37))  # 새로운 데이터로 predict() 할땐 데이터프레임의 형태로 주어야 한다
##        1 
## 28.93772
coef(fit1)[1] + coef(fit1)[2]*37  # 위의 결과와 동일.
## (Intercept) 
##    28.93772
predict(fit1, newdata = data.frame(kor=37), 
        interval="confidence")  # 신뢰구간
##        fit      lwr      upr
## 1 28.93772 27.70105 30.17439
predict(fit1, newdata = data.frame(kor=37), 
        interval="prediction")  # 예측구간
##        fit      lwr      upr
## 1 28.93772 23.85696 34.01847

11: 회귀 모형 도시하기

plot(kor,eng)
sorted.kor=sort(kor,index.return=TRUE)
s.kor=sorted.kor$x
s.eng=eng[sorted.kor$ix]
p<-predict(fit1,interval="confidence")
s.p<-p[sorted.kor$ix,]
abline(fit1,col="blue")
x<-c(s.kor,tail(s.kor,1),rev(s.kor),s.kor[1])
y<-c(s.p[,"lwr"],tail(s.p[,"upr"],1),
     rev(s.p[,"upr"]),s.p[,"lwr"][1])
polygon(x,y,col=rgb(0,1,0,0.25))

## 12: 회귀 모형 도시하기(conti.)
library(ggplot2)
q<-ggplot(data = data.frame(kor,eng), aes(x = kor, y = eng))
q

q + geom_point() + stat_smooth(method="lm")
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

13: 모형평가 차트

par(mfrow=c(2,2))
plot(fit1)

23: 일원배치법(반복수가 같은 경우)

A1 <- c(47,58,51,61,46)
A2 <- c(51,62,31,46,49) 
A3 <- c(50,38,47,27,23)
A4 <- c(22,23,28,42,25)
A <- c(A1,A2,A3,A4)

group <- as.factor(rep(1:4,each=5))
fabric <- data.frame(A,group) 
fabric
##     A group
## 1  47     1
## 2  58     1
## 3  51     1
## 4  61     1
## 5  46     1

## 7  62     2
## 8  31     2
## 9  46     2

## 12 38     3
## 13 47     3
## 14 27     3
## 15 23     3
## 16 22     4
## 17 23     4
## 18 28     4
## 19 42     4
## 20 25     4
A_table <- cbind(A1,A2,A3,A4) 
A_table

## [1,] 47 51 50 22
## [2,] 58 62 38 23
## [3,] 51 31 47 28
## [4,] 61 46 27 42

apply(A_table,2,mean)  # 열기준 평균

mean(A)

24: 일원배치법(반복수가 일정하지 않은 경우)

M1 <- c(2,3,4,5)
M2 <- c(4,5,6,4,3)
M3 <- c(6,5,7,4,6,8) 
M <- c(M1,M2,M3)

group_M <- as.factor(rep(1:3,times=c(4,5,6)))
mean(M1); mean(M2); mean(M3); mean(M)
## [1] 3.5
## [1] 4.4
## [1] 6
## [1] 4.8
mechanism<-data.frame(M,group_M)
aov_mechanism<-lm(M ~ group_M, data=mechanism)
anova(aov_mechanism)  # 분산분석표
## Analysis of Variance Table
## 
## Response: M
##           Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value  Pr(>F)  
## group_M    2   16.2  8.1000  4.8119 0.02921 *
## Residuals 12   20.2  1.6833                  
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1

28: 반복이 있는 이원배치법

machine <- factor(rep(1:3,each=6))
technician <- factor(rep(1:3,3,each=2))
quality <- c(9,14,14,16,19,22,13,16,18,
             26,14,18,11,12,11,17,15,16) 
product <- data.frame(machine,technician,quality) 
anova(lm(quality ~ machine * technician, data = product))
## Analysis of Variance Table
## 
## Response: quality
##                    Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value Pr(>F)

## machine:technician  4 74.222  18.556  2.0242 0.1744  
## Residuals           9 82.500   9.167                 
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
